---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How it works — Class6Loaner"
  description="How Class6Loaner builds calm, safety-first riders and connects experienced mentors with new riders through BorrowMyBike."
  canonicalPath="/how-it-works"
>
  <section class="card">
    <div class="muted" style="font-weight:900;">Simple. Predictable. Safety-first.</div>

    <h1 style="margin:8px 0 0; font-weight:1000;">
      How it works
    </h1>

    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; max-width:85ch;">
      Class6Loaner sets expectations and reduces uncertainty so test day feels predictable and safety-first. The marketplace (<a href="https://borrowmybike.ca" rel="noopener" target="_blank">BorrowMyBike</a>) runs the structured booking process, deposits, and status tracking.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- 1. EDUCATION FIRST -->
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">1. Calm, practical guidance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch;">
        We keep guidance practical and checklist-based so test day feels controlled — fewer unknowns, less stress, safer decisions.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>What to bring</li>
        <li>What to wear</li>
        <li>What happens on test day</li>
        <li>How to handle weather or unexpected issues</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. MENTORS STEP IN -->
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">2. Experienced riders step up</h2>

      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch;">
        Mentors help make test day calm and predictable.
        They are not instructors, and they are not running lessons.
        Road tests are booked under the assumption that the rider has already practiced.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Provide a road-test-ready bike</li>
        <li>Communicate clearly before the booking</li>
        <li>Show up prepared and on time</li>
        <li>Maintain a safety-first tone</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px; padding:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">What mentors don’t do</div>
        <ul style="margin-top:8px;">
          <li>No riding lessons</li>
          <li>No last-minute training sessions</li>
          <li>No promises about passing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. BOOKING FLOW -->
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">3. Booking happens on <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca" rel="noopener" target="_blank">BorrowMyBike</a></h2>

      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch;">
        When a rider has their date and time confirmed,
        they request a mentor and bike through the <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca" rel="noopener" target="_blank">BorrowMyBike</a> marketplace.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Request based on city</li>
        <li>Clear expectations before arrival</li>
        <li>Short, registry-based booking</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px; padding:14px;">
        <div style="font-weight:1000;">In-app messaging (peace of mind)</div>
        <div class="muted" style="margin-top:6px; max-width:85ch;">
          Mentors and test-takers can message in-app to coordinate timing, clarify expectations, and share quick safety tips. Once a booking is accepted, it’s confirmed and subject to platform policies.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:12px;">
        <a class="cta" href="https://borrowmybike.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Go to <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca" rel="noopener" target="_blank">BorrowMyBike</a> →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- NEW: Damage & responsibility (clear process) -->
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Damage &amp; responsibility</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch; margin:0;">
        Deposits are designed for accountability and to discourage no-shows — they do not guarantee full damage coverage.
        This is structured for short, registry-based road tests (not rentals or open riding).
      </p>

      <div class="muted" style="margin-top:12px; font-weight:900;">If something goes wrong (5 steps)</div>
      <ol class="muted" style="margin:6px 0 0; padding-left:18px; display:grid; gap:6px; max-width:95ch;">
        <li><b>Safety first.</b> Follow local requirements and call emergency services if needed.</li>
        <li><b>Document.</b> Take clear photos and note time/location (and any registry/examiner context if applicable).</li>
        <li>
         <b>Report by email.</b> Both parties email 
         <a href="mailto:support@borrowmybike.ca"><b>support@borrowmybike.ca</b></a> 
         as soon as reasonably possible with a short written summary and any photos.
        </li>
        <li><b>Review &amp; outcome.</b> We review both sides and apply the written platform rules. Damage/repair handling then follows the responsible party’s obligations and/or the standard insurance process.</li>
        <li><b>Close-out.</b> The booking is marked resolved; repeated unsafe or dishonest behavior can result in removal.</li>
      </ol>
        <p class="muted" style="margin-top:10px;">
          Full details: <a href="https://borrowmybike.ca/legal#damage" rel="noopener" target="_blank" style="font-weight:950; text-decoration: underline;">Damage &amp; responsibility →</a>
        </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. WHY THIS MATTERS -->
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Why this matters</h2>

      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch;">
        The goal isn’t just passing a test.
        The goal is building riders who start with a safety-first mindset —
        calm, aware, and responsible from day one.
      </p>

      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch; margin-top:10px;">
        When new riders begin their journey in a controlled, respectful, prepared environment,
        it benefits everyone on the road.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. MENTOR INCENTIVE SECTION -->
  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <div class="card">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">For experienced riders</h2>

      <p class="muted" style="max-width:85ch;">
        If you already own a suitable motorcycle and understand test-day expectations,
        you can help new riders start strong — and be compensated for your time,
        preparation, and professionalism.
      </p>

      <div style="margin-top:12px;">
        <a class="cta" href="/become-a-mentor">
          Become a mentor →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
